commit.message:
Add userhost-in-names capability (#1374)

Patch by: Geo
Fixes #1188

This updates channel records with hostmasks received from the userhost-in-names capability, and nothing more.

It also adds the isupport_get_prefixchars() function to get valid prefixchars from the 005 message, which we can use in other areas of the codebase now.

commit.message:
Properly report channel bans in .bans

Found by: @wilkowy
Patch by: Geo
Fixes: #1297

Prior to this patch, .bans was inconsistent. With a console of '*', Eggdrop only reported channels bans of the first channel in the channel record, and .bans #channel didn't report the bans on the requested channel.
